        <article><![CDATA[<div class="body conbody">
<div class="p">A search application configuration includes all search settings for a specific <span class="ph">Now Platform</span> application.
<ol id="define-search-app-config__ol_wpm_4lk_2nb" class="ol"><li class="li">Review the default search application configurations by following these steps.<br />
<ol id="define-search-app-config__ol_lx5_pyj_2nb" class="ol" type="a"><li class="li">Edit a search application configuration.</li><li class="li">Review the settings on the Search Application Configuration form and its related lists.</li><li class="li">To return to the list of search application configurations, click the Back icon.</li></ol>
</li><li class="li">Optionally, define new search application configurations as needed for your <span class="ph">AI Search</span> implementation by following these steps.<br />
<ol id="define-search-app-config__ol_a2x_5lk_2nb" class="ol" type="a"><li class="li">Click <strong><span class="ph uicontrol">New</span></strong>.</li><li class="li">On the Search Application Configuration form, fill in the fields.
<dl class="dl"><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Name</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Unique name for this search application configuration.</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Application ID</strong></dt><dd class="dd">ID for a <span class="ph">Now Platform</span> application.
<div class="note note"><strong><span class="notetitle">Note:</span></strong> In <span class="ph">Quebec</span>, only the following applications support <span class="ph">AI Search</span>: <span class="ph">Service Portal</span>, <span class="ph">Now Mobile</span>, and <span class="ph">Virtual Agent</span>.</div>
</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Search Profile</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Profile with the search experience you want to provide for users of the application.</dd></dl>
</li><li class="li">Click <strong><span class="ph uicontrol">Submit</span></strong>.</li></ol>
</li></ol>
</div>
</div>]]></article>
